Pine Script strategy builds the high and low of the first four hours of the New York session (9:00 AM–1:00 PM ET), locks that range after the 1:00 PM candle closes, and then trades breakouts based strictly on candle closes (wicks ignored). The strategy allows multiple breakouts per day, entering long when price closes above the NY range and short when it closes below, with configurable position sizing and risk-reward targets; stops can be set at the opposite side of the range or dynamically calculated. It works both for historical backtesting in the Strategy Tester and for live trading/alerts, making it suitable for intraday markets on lower timeframes such as 5- to 15-minute charts.
